criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria Patient Participants

          -  Age ≥65 years on the day of surgery;

          -  Scheduled major orthopedic surgery, or major surgical resection of a thoracic or
             abdominal malignancy, or major cardiac procedure;

          -  Clinically significant depression or anxiety symptoms screened by the PHQ-ADS (Patient
             Health Questionnaire Anxiety and Depression Scale) ≥10

        Exclusion Criteria Patient Participants

          -  Estimated life expectancy < 12 months;

          -  Unable to read, speak, and understand English;

          -  Current alcohol or other substance abuse;

          -  Severe cognitive impairment screened by the SBT (Short Blessed Test) >10;

          -  Acutely suicidal
